HEADWORD: Smithy
<hw>Smith"y</hw> <pr>(-⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>smi⟦edh⟧⟦edh⟧e</ets>, fr. <ets>smi⟦edh⟧</ets>; akin to D.
<ets>smidse</ets>, <ets>smids</ets>, OHG. <ets>smitta</ets>, G.
<ets>schmiede</ets>, Icel. <ets>smi⟦edh⟧ja</ets>. See <er>Smith</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>The workshop of a smith, esp. a blacksmith; a
smithery; a stithy.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>smiddy</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Under a spreading chestnut tree⟦br⟧
